00:00:55.199 --> 00:01:00.319
be repaired by nanobots, which are plentiful,
as they are programmed to periodically replicate

00:01:00.319 --> 00:01:05.320
themselves using whatever raw material is
at hand, such as the fibrous husk left over

00:01:05.320 --> 00:01:11.530
from rice milking. Unfortunately, the nanobots
have recently become self-aware, and have

00:01:11.530 --> 00:01:17.920
formed a union. They are now demanding higher
pay and shorter work hours. As a result, rice

00:01:17.920 --> 00:01:23.880
milk prices have skyrocketed. Fear not, vegan
hippies. Making your own rice milk at home

00:01:23.880 --> 00:01:30.820
is cheap, quick, and easy. I'll show you how.
First things first: grab a handful of rice,

00:01:30.820 --> 00:01:35.740
brown or white, and throw it into a pot. Grab
a handful of oatmeal and throw it into the

00:01:35.740 --> 00:01:43.729
same pot. Add several cups of water. Give
it a stir, turn the burner up to high, and

00:01:43.729 --> 00:01:51.600
bring it to a boil. Once it's boiling, stir
it once more, turn the burner down to low,

00:01:51.600 --> 00:01:56.630
put a lid on the pot, and let it simmer for
a while.

00:01:56.630 --> 00:02:01.270
Meanwhile, grab a handful of raw almonds,
sliced or whole, and throw them into a blender.

00:02:01.270 --> 00:02:06.789
If you don't like almonds, or are allergic,
you can skip this step. The almonds add flavor,

00:02:06.789 --> 00:02:12.130
nutrition, and give the milk a nice creamy
texture. Throw some water into the blender

00:02:12.130 --> 00:02:16.780
with the almonds and blend until smooth. As
far as flavor goes, you can substitute vanilla,

00:02:16.780 --> 00:02:25.350
whole bean or extract.
After they've simmered for a while, the rice

00:02:25.350 --> 00:02:29.420
and oatmeal should be soft and mushy. Let
them cool for a little bit, and then pour

00:02:29.420 --> 00:02:39.110
them into the blender with the almond mixture.
Add honey or the sweetener of your choice.

00:02:39.110 --> 00:02:42.830
